<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="76" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,962,579,604]" box="[151,962,579,604]" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">
<typeStatus box="[151,201,580,604]" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Radoszkowski, 1879" authorityName="Radoszkowski" authorityYear="1879" box="[294,679,579,603]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Mutilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="binotata">
<emphasis box="[294,459,579,603]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">Mutilla binotata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Radoszkowski, O." box="[466,679,579,603]" pageId="15" pageNumber="76" pagination="140 - 156" refId="ref19754" refString="Radoszkowski, O. (1879) Les Chrysides et Sphegides du Caucase. Horae Societatis Entomologicae Rossicae, 15 (2 - 3), 140 - 156." type="journal article" year="1879">Radoszkowski, 1879</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<specimenCount box="[690,709,580,603]" pageId="15" pageNumber="76" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
, by original designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,649,784]" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">
Three species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="1984" box="[346,496,650,675]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Macromyrme" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[346,496,650,675]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">Macromyrme</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occur in the Palaearctic and eleven species occur in the Afrotropical region (
<bibRefCitation author="Lelej, A. S." pageId="15" pageNumber="76" pagination="82 - 111" refId="ref18138" refString="Lelej, A. S. (2007) Biogeography of mutillid wasps (Hymenoptera, Mutillidae). In: Rasnitsyn, A. P. &amp; Gokhman, V. E. (Eds.), Studies on Hymenopterous Insects. Collection of Scientific Papers. KMK Scientific Press Ltd., Moscow, pp. 82 - 111. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="2007">Lelej 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="El-Torkey, A. M. &amp; Oshaibah, A. D. A. &amp; Salem, M. M. H. &amp; Hosni, M. T. &amp; Abdel-Rhman, A. - R. G. &amp; Soliman, A. M." box="[222,461,685,711]" pageId="15" pageNumber="76" pagination="63 - 68" refId="ref16752" refString="El-Torkey, A. M., Oshaibah, A. D. A., Salem, M. M. H., Hosni, M. T., Abdel-Rhman, A. - R. G. &amp; Soliman, A. M. (2011) Review of the Palaearctic species of Macromyrme Lelej 1984 (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae) with description of a new species from Egypt. Zootaxa, 2863 (1), 63 - 68. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2863.1.4" type="journal article" year="2011">
El-Torkey 
<emphasis box="[341,397,685,711]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lo Cascio, P. &amp; Romano, M. &amp; Grita, F." box="[473,716,685,712]" pageId="15" pageNumber="76" pagination="525 - 544" refId="ref18662" refString="Lo Cascio, P., Romano, M. &amp; Grita, F. (2012) New species and new records of mutillid wasps from the Socotra Archipelago (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 52 (Supplement), 525 - 544." type="journal article" year="2012">
Lo Cascio 
<emphasis box="[593,649,685,711]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
). The male is still unknown for this genus. One species occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[151,278,721,747]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
. Because of a new synonymy, we include in the list 
<taxonomicName authority="(Klug)" baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[851,1046,721,748]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Macromyrme" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis box="[851,963,721,747]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">M. villosa</emphasis>
(Klug)
</taxonomicName>
, which is absent in 
<collectingCountry box="[1260,1386,721,747]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
, and prepared a key to all Palaearctic species of this genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
